name: Baked Ranch Tilapia Burgers
author: epoor
summary: These super easy fish burgers are a great, wholesome meal. Assemble buns with whatever you please. I prefer to eat the tilapia with lettuce only but my boyfriend puts ketchup and cheese on his. We always eat this with steamed broccoli and fruit salad.
ingredients: 1 ½ teaspoons dry ranch seasoning mix, or to taste
½ cup shredded lettuce, or to taste
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Spread olive oil on a baking sheet
Mix bread crumbs and ranch dressing mix in a second bowl
Submerge tilapia in the egg, remove, and coat with bread crumb mixture
Place breaded tilapia on the baking sheet
Bake in the preheated oven until fish flakes easily with a fork, about 15 minutes
Assemble fillets on hamburger buns and top with lettuce
